ðŸ” Merge vs. Append
â€¢	Merge: Combines columns from two tables based on matching keys (like SQL joins).
âž¤ Example: Merge Orders and Customers on CustID.
â€¢	Append: Combines rows from two or more tables with the same structure (columns).
âž¤ Example: Append Orders_Jan and Orders_Feb.
